AR10 - Stage Depeyre Morand Architectures

A first six-month internship with the Parisian architectural firm Depeyre Morand Architectures proved to be an enriching immersion in the world of architecture. This multi-disciplinary experience was distinguished by the diversity of the assignments entrusted to us, enabling us to develop a wide range of skills, from graphic design to the processing of administrative documents.Among the projects carried out during this period, illustrative posters were designed to present a garden project for a sheltered residence. These visuals were intended to showcase the efforts made to create a garden in the residents’ own image, which they would be able to care for themselves.A series of summary models in plaster and brass was also produced. These models, precise and detailed, illustrated a succession of punctual interventions within the city of Paris. One notable assignment was to draw up a preliminary design for an extension including six apartments for a sheltered residence. This work involved the preliminary stages of design, from site analysis to the formulation of architectural proposals, while integrating regulatory constraints and the needs of future occupants.